m/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23447.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Loosing buffs when you zone low on life - TEST + HYPOTHE</span><hr size=1> From my observations the gear you wear isn't where the problem comes... its particular types of buffs, most often the shielding line.<br>
<br>
Some HP buffs will leave you &quot;wounded&quot; after they are cast, such as the shielding line for casters (or Dain hammer click.)<br>
Other HP buffs will &quot;fill in&quot; those gained HP, such as the cleric line of hero, reso, etc... this set of buffs can actually be used for healing since refreshing them adds the HP back each time.<br>
<br>
It's that first set, from my observations, that causes the problem. Any time you zone with damage into those HP you appear to lose all buffs. As a ranger, this buff loss problem never once happened to me proir to the addition of the &quot;Strength of Nature&quot; spell being added. Those 75hp fall into that first catagory, and I've noticed this buff loss issue happen when zoning that low.<br>
<br>
I disagree with the &quot;the mob hit you after the LOADING PLEASE WAIT thus resulting in your death&quot; theory. I've had it happen without any mobs around, simply being ported after having manastoned too far.<br>
<br>
To test, duel someone while standing next to a zone line... Let them get you down to single digit hp, then zone. Do this once totally unbuffed (in terms of added hp.. use SoW, resist whatever, haste, etc to know if any buffs were lost.)  Do this a second time with a shielding style spell as a HP buff (and toss on a few &quot;junk buffs&quot; so you can see if you lost everything.) Repeat again with a second catagory buff (reso, hero, skin like anything-but-wood.)  To verify is +hp gear factors in, can repeat this test with and without +hp gear.<br>
<br>
(skin like wood falls into first group, a shielding style buff... i suppose it was &quot;too good&quot; of a heal for lower characters.)<br>
<br>
<br>
I wouldn't totally rule out +hp gear, but leveling my monk I never noticed it occur and I'd had probably 200-250hp in items. (+stam might be the problem though)<br>
<br>
