<br>
the game strips you of all your equipment when you zone, then build it back up again on the other side.<br>
<br>
Suppose you have<br>
1000hp base<br>
100hp from equipment bonuses<br>
<br>
You zone with 150hp.  <br>
The game strips your equipment and their bonuses.  <br>
You zone naked with 50hp safely.  <br>
The game builds your gear back up, and you end up on other side with 150hp, untouched.<br>
<br>
You zone with 50hp.  <br>
The game strips your equipment and their bonuses.<br>
You zone naked with -50hp.<br>
You die while zoning, and lose all buffs.<br>
As a design feature to prevent people coming up as a corpse after zoning, the game adjusts your hp so it's +ve and you don't die.<br>
The game builds your gear back up, and you end up on other side with some amount of hp left, but your buffs were lost from dying.<br>
<br>
